### Endpoints to implement

```
POST /healthstack/login
    Body: { email, password }
    Returns: { token, role, name }
    Logic: check _USERS dict, call _make_token(email, role)

GET  /healthstack/services
    No auth required
    Returns: { providers: _PROVIDERS }

POST /healthstack/book
    require_role(["patient"])
    Body: { provider_id, slot }
    Creates new booking entry in _BOOKINGS (append to list)
    Returns: { booking_id, provider_name, slot, price, status: "Confirmed" }

POST /healthstack/checkout
    require_role(["patient"])
    Body: { booking_id, card_last4 }
    Fake PaymentIntent: "pi_demo_" + secrets.token_hex(6)
    Update booking status to "Paid"
    Returns: { payment_intent_id, amount, status: "succeeded", confirmation: booking_id }

GET  /healthstack/dashboard/patient
    require_role(["patient"])
    Returns only bookings where patient_email == request.hs_user["email"]
    Returns: { user_name, bookings: [...] }

GET  /healthstack/dashboard/admin
    require_role(["admin"])
    Returns all bookings + audit log + patient roster (initials only)
    Returns: { total_bookings, total_patients, bookings: [...], audit_log: _AUDIT_LOG,
               patients: [{ initials: "J.D.", specialty: "...", last_visit: "..." }] }

POST /healthstack/upload
    require_role(["patient"])
    Stub: just returns { success: True, file_id: "file_" + secrets.token_hex(4) }
    No actual file handling needed
```

