## 4. Demo App (CDN React 18 via esm.sh)

### index.html imports

```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
<script type="module" src="app.js"></script>
```

### app.js ES module imports

```js
import React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'https://esm.sh/react@18'
import { createRoot } from 'https://esm.sh/react-dom@18/client'
```

Use `createRoot` (React 18 API), not `ReactDOM.render`.

### api.js base URL

```js
const BASE = 'https://api.michaelwegter.com/healthstack'

function authHeaders() {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('hs_token')
  return token ? { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
               : { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
}

export async function login(email, password) { ... }
export async function getServices() { ... }
export async function book(providerId, slot) { ... }
export async function checkout(bookingId, cardLast4) { ... }
export async function getPatientDashboard() { ... }
export async function getAdminDashboard() { ... }
export async function uploadFile(file) { ... }
export function logout() { localStorage.removeItem('hs_token'); localStorage.removeItem('hs_role'); }
```

### State machine (hash-router pattern)

State: `{ view, token, role, userName, selectedProvider, bookingResult }`

Views: `login | services | slot-picker | checkout | confirmation | patient-dash | admin-dash`

No React Router needed. Use a simple top-level state variable for current view and render
the matching component.

