## 7. Design Implementation Notes

### Color usage in healthstack demo
- Background shell: `#121118` (--bg-root)
- Cards: `#1e1c26` (--bg-card), border `#2c2a38` (--border-default)
- Primary CTA "Book" / "Pay": `#e8b820` (--mustard), dark text `#121118`
- Provider card accent bar (left border): `#12b4c8` (--cyan-vivid)
- Admin role badge: `#f0186e` (--hot-pink)
- Patient role badge: `#12b4c8` (--cyan-vivid)
- Booking confirmation checkmark: `#6ed46a` (--parrot-green)
- Error states: `#e83828` (--parrot-red)
- Text primary: `#f2ede4`, secondary: `#8a8898`, muted: `#4a4858`

### Typography
- "HealthStack" logo: Space Grotesk 700, "Health" in --mustard, "Stack" in --text-primary
- Section eyebrows: font-family JetBrains Mono / monospace, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.1em, --text-muted
- Body: Inter
- Price chips, badge text: monospace

### Trust signals (visual, easy wins)
- Small lock icon + "TLS 1.3" chip in the header right side
- Footer chip: `Demo: PHI handling follows minimum-necessary principle`
- Admin dashboard: orange "PHI Minimized" label on the patient roster column

