## 10. Stack Framing for Deck / Cover Letter

The demo uses React 18 (CDN) + mw-backend Flask JWT. In the proposal, frame it accurately:

- "The demo runs React 18 and communicates with a live Flask API that enforces
  role-based JWT auth, which is the same access-control pattern I apply with
  Supabase RLS in production Next.js projects."
- "In a real build, this becomes: Next.js App Router + Supabase Auth (server-side
  session) + Row Level Security policies. The demo proves I understand the
  access-control model, not just the toolchain."
- Stripe: "The checkout modal in the demo shows the UX flow and calls a mock
  endpoint. Production uses Stripe.js + server-side PaymentIntents, Stripe webhooks
  for status updates, and Stripe Customer Portal for subscription management."
- Vercel: "Next.js deploys to Vercel with environment variables for Supabase and
  Stripe keys, preview deployments on every PR, and Edge Runtime where latency matters."

